Product name: Vintage 1976 Locket | Vintage Locket | 1970s Locket | Vintage Bird Locket | Silver Locket | Rose Gold Locket | Large Oval Silver Locket
Description:
Vintage 1976 silver oval locket featuring beautiful etched leaf swirls and flourishes with a rose gold bird in flight. Within the locket there are two compartments which allow you to place a picture, lock of hair or a thin momento would be able to fit into the locket. The hallmarks on the back of locket indicates the piece hallmarked in 1976 from silver in Birmingham by JS (Joseph Smith & Sons).
HISTORY
The Locket has a long rich history, during the earlier centuries, they were used to carry good luck charms, mementoes, hair, powder and even poison. The locket secured its romantic status during the Victorian era, it became the most mysterious and alluring pieces of jewellery. Only the wearer knows what secrets lie within the locket. It was to be the ultimate love token. Pictures held in lockets were originally miniature portraits, these were gradually replaced with photographs.
HALLMARKS
JS (Joseph Smith & Sons), Anchor, Lion, Letter 'B'.
MEASUREMENTS
The necklace measures 4.1cm / 1.6" in height, 3.2cm / 1.2" in width, 8mm / 0.3" in thickness. The locket hangs from a 51.5cm / 20.2" in length.
CONDITION
Excellent

Product name: 1800s Men's Vest 1860s Vest 1870s Vest Silk Vest Civil War Vest Original 1800s 1800s Clothing 19th Century Mens Vest 19th Century Clothing
Description:
This listing is for a beautiful original 1800's men's silk vest! Finding original clothing from this period is getting rarer and rarer, so to find one that's in relatively good condition is even better!
The vest bears all of the hallmark style points that lead us to believe it's from the 1860's or 1870's, and is approximately Civil War-era. It has a silk front with a shawl collar and fabric-covered buttons. The back and inside lining appears to be cotton.
It is in very old, but good, condition, especially for its age. The silk does have some discolouration, as does the cotton. There is some staining under the arm holes from sweat (pretty typical of clothing from this period). All of the buttons are present and intact, though they do have some discolouration and a few are stained. The top buttonhole has some light damage immediately to its right. 
The belt in the back is intact and even has a brass buckle with an 1855 patent date! (See photo for details!)
Initials (presumably those from the original owner) are written in what appears to be pencil inside. They are "P.G."
There is a repair under the right arm hole (see photo). We are unsure if this was done in-period or was a later addition. We do not have any blacklight capability to test it under UV at this time and did not want to risk damaging the integrity of the garment by performing a burn test on the thread used for the repair, so we are unsure as to the period of said repair, sorry. There are a few other small nips in the fabric in various places.
While quite old, the vest does appear to still be wearable, if only lightly, though we recommend using it simply as a study piece or to possibly gauge a pattern from.
That said, there is no size anywhere on the vest, so our measurements are as follow:
Across chest, pit to pit (buttoned, lying flat): 19.5"
Overall length, from bottom of collar to bottom hem in back: 21"

Product name: Flower painting, vintage oil painting, still life, still life painting, oil painting, flower still life, vintage still life, vintage flower
Description:
I have recently found two beautiful oil paintings from an art collector in Utrecht that is downsizing his collection.
This floral still life is vibrant and comes in a beautiful frame. The painting is oil on canvas, then pasted onto a wood panel. This is called the Marouflé technique. It  is signed J. Molenaar. Most likely, this has been painted by the artist Johannes Petrus (Joop) Molenaar. The collector believes it was painted by that artist in the 1940s. Joop Molenaar is best known for his paintings of shipyards and harbor views, but this painting was so vibrant, colorful, and happy I couldn't pass it up!
Height: 21.5 inches
Width: 17.5 inches
Please note there are some signs of age that can be seen in the photos. At the top left of the painting the wood panel, and consequently the painting, is chipped. This is not obvious from a distance, but I do need to disclose that. It can be seen in photo 4.
The second thing to note is there are small marks on the very left edge of the painting where it looks like a nail that holds the painting in the frame rubbed against it. Please see photo 5. Finally, the frame has a crack in the lower left hand corner as well as the upper right hand corner- to me it adds character, but I do want to point that out.
When I got the painting there was duck tape on the back to hold the panel in the frame in addition to the nails that are usually found. I have chosen to let the buyer decide if they want to remove it or not- it does have a sturdy wire across the back and is ready for hanging.
The price does reflect these few blemishes. I hope to find a good home for this beautiful piece.
Please message me with any questions.

Product name: Luxury Nose Work Mat- Snuffle Mat -Dog Playmat - Dog Blanket  (size 41"x58")
Description:
This 100% hand-made Luxury Nose Work Mat will be a fun and interactive toy to challenge your dog physically and mentally.
Hide your dog's favorite treats or toys and train them to search for it by its smell, helping the dog build self-esteem in a fun and healthy way! Your dog will love this mat from the memory of finding his/her treats and toys! 
check out the video Evie playing on the mat at 
*******https://m.facebook.com/eviesbarkyard/?hc_ref=NEWSFEED******
·Activities designed and hand made from scratch
·Different level activities with versatile uses
·Easily rollable with sewn-in ties for compact storage
.Available in three sizes
      -SMALL MAT: 20.5"X36" up to 12lbs
      -MEDIUM MAT:  32"x41" up to 30lbs
      -LARGE MAT: 41.5"x58" up to 65lbs 
** Note: a large size mat shown in the images with a 12 pound terrier dog 
 
______________________________
What is Nose Work?
Created in 2006, Nose Work is an easy-to-learn search and scenting activity or competitive sport that can help build your dog’s confidence and focus; no prior training or obedience needed. Shy or fearful dogs can build confidence and overactive dogs can put their energy into fun searches as they learn independent problem-solving skills and are disciplined through training. Cooperation between trainer and dog will build stronger bonds and relationships. The new urban sport of Nose Work is for dogs of all ages, personalities, and sizes!
Official Association (not sponsored): https://www.nacsw.net 
Instructions:
1. While your dog is preoccupied with a different activity, hide their favorite toys or treats in different compartments of the mat.
2. After completion, have your dog smell another one of their toys with their saliva scent or the same treat.
3. Release your dog onto the mat. If your dog is having trouble locating the designated object, pat around the general area of the target to encourage the dog to search or sniff. (This is more likely to happen if it is one of the dog’s first sessions)
4. After one to two sessions (varies per dog), the dog will need little to no guidance and the mat may be used a preoccupation during your absence.
WASHING INSTRUCTIONS: Spot wash preferred for maximum lifetime. If to be machine washed, use cold water and gentle wash individually. Do not tumble dry! 
DISCLAIMER: This mat is not advertised as indestructible. Despite its versatility, after prolonged use it will eventually wear, tear, and break. Not recommended for over 65 lb dogs.

The art of Samantha Wortelhock – whether fine-art paintings or large public murals – is naïve, untutored, purely instinctive. She is an artist because she is a dreamer and storyteller.
  
In January, 1988, the year of bicentenary, Sam left the UK to travel to Australia, lured by stories of a primordial land and an ancient culture, and encouraged by a partner who had spent an idyllic childhood in Sydney. She found the city seemingly devoid of Aboriginality, yet the coastal landscape captivated her eager spirit and spoke of a hidden secret.
  
And so Sam started to paint – each night “requesting” a dream that would lead to a painting. On the night of her 22nd birthday, she dreamt her first painting, Balance. It was to become the blueprint for a collection of art that has captivated, educated and inspired many disparate groups of people to look more closely into Aboriginality and the value of preserving our natural world - intricate chronicles full of humour, insight and respect.
 
Sam’s art took her quickly to the pinnacle of commercial success, including fetching record prices in regional Australia. She was the brains behind the Mulgara Gallery at Uluru and established and owned Heaven and Earth Gallery in Sydney’s Queen Victoria Building and Field of Dreams in Queen Street Woollahra. 
Today, Sam has expanded her focus from original paintings, lithographs and Giglee prints and has ventured more into vivid and eye-catching murals both for schools and for community; portraits on a commissioned basis; and contributed paintings to books.
If interested in purchasing Giglee canvas prints or Original Paintings of Sam’s work, you can purchase on www.breakawayart.com.au.

Description:
This unusual  musical Russian cathedral "Basil" nesting doll is hand-crafted from wood and hand painted by a talented Russian artist.

 When you turn it on the Russian cathedral "Basil"will rotate and you will hear a famous Russian song ”Moscow Nights"
Brilliant Present!

Cathedral of the Mantle of Our Lady, also known as Saint Basil's Cathedral is an Orthodox Temple located on the Red Square in Moscow. It is a widely known monument of Russian architecture. Until the XVII century it was commonly called the Trinity Cathedral, as the original wooden church was dedicated to the Holy Trinity. The temple was also known as Jerusalem Cathedral due to the dedication of one of the chapels, as well as the being the destination for the Patriarch's religious procession from the Cathedral of the Assumption on Palm Sunday, called the Donkey Walk. St. Basil's Cathedral was built in 1555-1561 by the order of Ivan IV (the Terrible) to commemorate the capture of Kazan and the victory over the Kazan Khanate, which happened exactly on the day of the Intercession of the Mother of God - in the beginning of October 1552. As the legend has it, the architects of the cathedral (Barma and Postnik) were blinded by the order of Ivan the Terrible, so they could never build another such temple.

Product name: Custom LED Lightsaber Style 2
Description:
Unlike many sabers you will find, this saber is fully customizable using the MHS system. This means that you can keep upgrading, change the hilt design, or change the electronics. Some of the features include: a very bright Cree Star LED, aircraft grade aluminum hilt, and an extremely durable, removable Polycarbonate blade. This is an excellent option if you want something that is both well-constructed and affordable.
         If you are interested in seeing a demo of this Lightsaber with the 4x AAA with Sound option, check out this quick video where a demonstrate a few of the sounds and how to take remove the chassis to change the battery's.
 https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=8NGvJWm8CEk
	If you plan on doing little or no sparring then I would recommend the 4 AAA battery pack but if you are planning on sparring a lot then the 18650 would be the best option. Both the  18650 option and the 4x AAA option also include a very nice chassis system which enhances the durability and overall niceness of the saber. On average 4 AAA will last around 1 hour vs. an 18650 which will last almost 3 hours. Also note the 4x AAA with Sound option comes with a basic sound board and the 18650 with Sound option includes the Nano Biscotti sounds board which is much better and includes a removable SD card. For more info on the Nano Biscotti follow this link. http://www.thecustomsabershop.com/Nano-Biscotte-Sound-Module-V3-P806.aspx
	If you wish to have your saber customized more than the available options please contact me and I will try to accommodate any requests you have. 
        In the box: Hilt with Electronics pre-installed, 32" Blade, Allen Wrench, Retention Screw, and, depending on which battery setup you select, either 4 AAA Batteries or an 18650 battery with a charger.
  Thanks for taking the time to check this out and if you have any questions please contact me and I will get back with you as soon as possible.

Product name: Custom Engagement/ Wedding Scrapbook Album
Description:
If your engagement photo shoot was anything like mine, you ended up with dozens upon dozens of photos you loved, but had no place to display them all! This is the perfect solution for those who love displaying their photos and don’t want to use just any boring album. 
The albums I create are not your stereotypical scrapbooks. In addition to individually matting each photo with cardstock, I use handmade and artisanal papers I find at stationary and bookbinding stores. I never use the typical patterned and themed papers you find at craft stores. I take special care to make each and every page classy and elegant!
The 350 price includes:
Cost of prints
Supplies (e.g., cardstock, fine papers, washi tape, embellishments, alphabet stickers, ribbons, etc.)
20 12”x12” pages (If you need more pages, I charge 15 per page over 20; for five or more extra pages, I charge 10 per page)
How the process works:
Let me know the color scheme you’d like
Pick out up to 50 photos. This averages to about 2.5 photos per page, which allows for a wide variety of layouts and photos per page. 
Just e-mail me the photos and I’ll take care of the rest (cropping, black and whites, printing)! 
I also do custom wedding scrapbooks so be sure to check out my other listing!

Product name: Samsonite Padded Camera Bag, Camera Case,  Vintage 1990
Description:
This is a black fabric, feels like nylon, padded camera case.  I wouldn’t consider this a large bag, although it is larger than the new “Samsonite Large Point and Shoot Camera Case” is saw on Amazon.  Yet it is still really small enough and light enough to be easily manageable.  The outside dimension is  about 7 x 7 inches, inside dimension 6 ½ x 6 ½. .  The large back compartment has a padded divider that can be removed to make the one large compartment, or attached to Velcro strips that run almost the whole width of the compartment to divide it into two compartments of almost any size you need. The zipper closing this large section of the case has a little collar that folds snugly down to hide the zipper, then both are covered by the large flap that attaches to a piece of Velcro; increasing the weather-proof qualities of the case. 
There is a front panel that unzips to fold out revealing a mesh pocket, 3 x 2 ½ inches, 4 elastic loops for holding whatever, and three small fabric pockets, with access from the side and elastic along the edge to keep whatever is inside secure.  One outside edge has an additional mesh pocket about 4 ½ inches deep and 2 ½ in wide.  The last of the four elastic loops has some loose stitching.  I believe it must have been a manufacturing defect because I’m quite sure I never used the loops for anything.  That is the only flaw I find. 
The adjustable, detachable shoulder strap is about 47 inches long when fully extended; it’s clean with no fraying.  There is a purse type handle firmly stitched to the top if you prefer to carry it that way, or you can attach it to your belt, backpack or even your golf cart via the strap on the back, stitched at the top and attached by Velcro at the bottom.  There is a small white tag sewn into an inside seam that may be a model #  PO:001392 FID40.

Product name: Low Poly Paper Model, 3D Rocket Papercraft, Low Poly Spaceship, 3D Papercraft Sculpture - DIY Printable PDF Template
Description:
Blast Off Rocket 3D Papercraft, Low Poly Spaceship Sculpture - DIY Printable PDF Template
Get ready for take off with this unique papercraft sculpture of a rocketship soaring skywards on a streaming vapour trail.  We designed the rocket to reflect a classic 1950's design style yet the entire sculpture has a contemporary vibe. Dynamic and free-standing, this 3D paper model will add a taste of adventure to any man cave or office.  As this product is a printable template you can tailor the colour of the finished sculpture to your own home decor.  A sculpture handcrafted by you from our template will make a great personalised gift for a sci-fi fan, kid's bedroom or that special person in your life.
The PDF template and assembly guide are supplied as instant downloads so there are no shipping charges and no need to wait for the delivery truck, you can start creating today!  As this sculpture is made from a printable template you can show off your own creativity by printing the components on coloured cardstock to create your own unique colour scheme.  
All our photographs show real-life papercraft sculptures and not computer-generated  mock-ups. You can see more images of our work in our About Us section.
\\ What You Will Receive
•	PDF Template in black and white
•	PDF Illustrated Assembly Guide in English language
You receive the two PDF files as digital downloads, no physical product will be shipped to you meaning no shipping charges or waiting time! 
Once you have downloaded the files you can print out the PDFs on a standard home printer (you will need PDF reader software such as Adobe Reader to open them). The templates are designed to fit US Letter size paper (8.5 x 11 inches) however they can also be printed using A4 (210mm x 297mm) paper size.
\\ PDF Template Details
Assembly Time:  A couple of afternoons or evenings (about 8 hours).
Difficulty level: 5 (Challenging - Best suited to experienced papercrafters)
Approximate dimensions of the finished sculpture from template:
•	Height  19.5 inches (495mm)
•	Width  13 inches (330mm)
•	Depth 7.7 inches (195mm)
\\ Additional items you will need:
•	Cardstock 
•	Printer
•	PDF Viewer software such as Adobe Reader
•	Scissors and hobby knife (for scoring)
•	Ruler
•	Either PVA glue or high-tack double sided sticky tape
\\ How to assemble
Once you have printed out the template, just cut out the parts then score and fold them. After this comes the fun part, watching your sculpture come to life as you stick it together! We have carefully designed and tested the template for an enjoyable crafting experience. You can also find our video guide to assembling papercraft sculptures here https://youtu.be/k9j8HYASC4g
\\ Payment Options
 
We accept payment through Etsy by credit card or PayPal. 
Your item will be available for download immediately after the payment is confirmed. If you have not purchased a digital item from Etsy before there is a helpful guide on how to download it at this link (https://www.etsy.com/uk/help/article/3949).
\\ Returns and Exchanges
As this is a digital download we cannot accept returns, exchanges or cancellations. If you have any questions or have any problems with your downloaded item, please see our FAQ section below or convo us and we will try to help.
\\ Additional information
Kablackout paper sculptures are not designed to be assembled by children under 12 years of age.

Animals and birds are a significant feature in Celtic and Norse mythology. Animals and birds were vital to everyday life and wellbeing and they feature in art, literature, rituals and religious beliefs. 
In Celtic mythology the Raven features in many legends. This large bird feeding as it does on carrion with its black plumage and disturbing deep hoarse croak is often viewed with some foreboding for it can be seen as an omen of death. It can also be associated as a source of power, straddling as it does the worlds of the living and the dead therefore often depicted as messenger between the two. Ravens hovering over the scenes of battle, ready to swoop down on the bodies of the fallen must have been a fearsome sight to Celtic warriors. Little wonder then that they could be seen as having the power of gods.

Description:
Men ring. I love rings on men. I love men who wears jewelry. I love cool jewelry on men! 
Sterling silver (925) ring is open at the front for an edgy look but still keeping low-profile!
This ring is slightly textured all around and the inside is brushed. Don't hesitate asking initiales to be written inside or a special date to remember or anything small you'd like!
***925 silver is the most common and good quality silver used for jewelry. Most people aren't allergic to silver and can be worn easily. Each jewelry comes in a beautiful wrapping, including a silver towel to freshen the jewelry once in a while. I recommend to keep your silver jewelry in a box, in a dry room. Avoid wearing natural pearls in shower and chlorine water. Natural pearls like fresh water and salt water! But they will last longer away from chemicals, perfume and scented cream!
As it is all hand made and hand cut, the average time to make an order is 2-3 weeks. BUT! I would be so happy to help you more if you need a jewelry in a short time or personalized!
-----------------------
Jonc pour homme.  J'adore les bagues sur les hommes. J'adore les hommes qui portent des bijoux. J'aime les bijoux sur les hommes!
Fait en argent sterling (925) le jonc est ouverte sur le dessus pour donner un 'edge' au simple jonc mais tout en gardant une simplicité! 
Le jonc a une texture légère tout autour et l'intérieur est fini à la brosse. N'hésitez pas à demander des initiales, une date importante à se rappeler inscrit à l'intérieur! 
***L'argent 925 est l'argent de qualité le plus utilisé pour les bijoux. La majorité des gens ne sont pas allergique à l'argent et l'argent se porte facilement. Chaque bijou est soigneusement enveloppé et vient avec une serviette pour nettoyer l'argent et les métaux précieux afin de rafraichir votre bijou de temps en temps. Je recommande de garder vos bijoux en argent sterling dans une boite, dans un endroit sec. Évitez de porter les perles naturelles dans la douche et dans l'eau chlorée. Les perles naturelles aiment l'eau douce et salée mais elles resteront belles plus longtemps éloigné des parfums, synthétiques et crèmes parfumées!
Elles sont entièrement fait à la main et le temps d'une commande est d'environ 2-3 semaines. MAIS! Je serais plus qu'heureuse de vous aider si vous avez besoin d'un bijou plus rapidement ou personnalisé.

Product name: Hot Pink Shorts with a Black Waistband - Spandex Dance Shorts Comfortable and Stylish. All Sizes Available
Description:
Pink and Black...the color combination that is all the rage. These shorts go with any leotard or shirt, 
And of course, a dance top can be made to match, to make it into a complete outfit!!!
These shorts are a made from a light/medium weight 4-way stretch spandex, and cut from the famous Dance Mom's Dance Wear pattern that fits the way a dancer WANTS them to fit! 
Matching Sports Bra tops can be made to match these shorts!
The girls at our studio used to complain that the dance shorts they bought did not fit right! They were too long in the crotch, but when they folded down the waistband, they came up too high and gave them a "wedgie!"
So I created this pattern...and the girls love it!
These shorts are made to fit comfortably just below the waist, and have a Spandex waistband with NO ELASTIC!!!!
_______________________________________________________________________
ABOUT DANCE MOM'S DANCE WEAR:
I am a Dance Mom.
Back when I was toting my kids back and forth to the studio, we didn't have a name for it, but that's what I was...a Dance Mom. In fact...I had 9 kids who danced! I was a Dance Mom Extraordinaire! 
When I was a dance mom, there was no "Dance Moms" television show. We didn't have a balcony to sit in, and we didn't yell and bicker.
When I was a dance mom, we sat on folding chairs outside the studio. We looked after our younger children and we exchanged recipes....and I became the official "fixer of costumes," because the kids hated the way their dance wear fit!
They hated the elastic waistbands that pinched and pulled when they danced. They hated the "baggy butt syndrome" they got when they wore their dance shorts, and the "wedgie" they got when they turned down the waistband. 
Mostly, they generally disliked the fact that while all dancers are different, the costumes are made in "cookie cutter" fashion, with different SIZES, but not different "FITS." 
It is through this experience that I learned what dancers like, and how to fit different body types. I developed my special dance shorts pattern that is exclusive to this site, with a fit that is flattering for dancers from 3 years old to 30.
I learned how to make a "washable tutu" so that the little ones can play dress up without having to throw away their favorite tutu when it gets dirty.
And I learned that there is nothing to be gained by using cheap spandex. Quality is important to the way dance wear fits and holds up through the rigourous testing of a serious dancer.
At THIS dance mom's dance wear store, we care about how your dance wear fits, and that you get the quality that you deserve.
And if you happen to see an episode of that "Dance Mom's" show, and you see an outfit on one of the dancers that you would like to have made...let me know. I just LOVE those special orders!
If you have any questions, feel free to contact me.
